SIMPLE: processional
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Processional
<hw>Pro*ces"sion*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Of or
pertaining to a procession; consisting in a procession.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The <qex>processional</qex> services became more frequent.</q>
<rj><qau>Milman.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Processional</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Processional
<hw>Pro*ces"sion*al</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>processionnal</ets>, LL. <ets>processionale</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld> <def>A service book relating to
ecclesiastical processions.</def> <rj><au>J. Gregory.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A hymn, or other selection, sung during a church
procession; <as>as, the <ex>processional</ex> was the 202d
hymn</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Processionalist</ent>⟦br⟧
